metaphor: help repair the ship, but only if you have the right tool for the job
scene_description: the background is made of black pixels. there is a rough green rectangle near the center of the grid that stretches from the top to the bottom. on the edges of the rectangle, there are gaps of various sizes. there are 5 other shapes in the grid of different colors. in order of size, the colors of the shapes are as follows: a blue shape of 8 pixels, a red shape of 10 pixels, a pink shape of 10 pixels, a yellow shape of 12 pixels, and a cyan shape of 13 pixels.
literal_instruction: make two larger shapes by combining the various existing shapes. the pieces cannot rotate. build the first shape by moving the red shape left 6 spaces so that it is flush with the green rectangle. then, move the yellow shape so that it melds flush with the red shape. for the final step for the 1st new shape, move the blue shape so that it melds flush with the yellow shape. on the right side of the green rectangle there should now be a new shape composed, from left to right, of red pixels, yellow pixels, and blue pixels. for the 2nd shape, move the cyan shape into the top notch of the green rectangle on the left side. it should be flush with the green rectangle. then, move the pink shape so that it melds flush with the cyan shape. from right to left starting from the green rectangle, the new shape should go from cyan to pink.
